        <section id="collection-john-herrman" class="john-herrman-collection collection" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/CollectionPage">
        <header class="collection-header">
        <div class="collection-meta">
            <div class="collection-meta-header">
    <div class="supported-by nocontent robots-nocontent hidden">
    <span class="ad-label">Supported by</span>
    <div id="SupportedBy" class="supported-by-ad ad"></div>
</div>    <h3 class="kicker">
        <span class="kicker-label">
            <a href=""></a>
        </span>
            </h3>
</div><!-- close collection-meta-header -->
            <div class="collection-meta-group">

                
                <div class="collection-headings">

    <div class="collection-heading-group">

                                 
            <h1 class="collection-heading" itemprop="name">
                John Herrman            </h1>
                                        <div class="follow-button-placeholder" style="" data-collection-id="byline.john-herrman"></div>
                    
            </div><!-- close collection-heading-group -->

    
    
            <h2 class="collection-subheading" itemprop="about">John Herrman covers media for The New York Times Magazine. Previously, he was a reporter for the Business section and one of the first three recipients of The Times's David Carr Fellowship.                        <a class="user-action">More<i class="icon caret-icon"></i></a>
                    </h2>
    
    
</div><!-- close collection-headings -->

            </div>
        </div>
            </header>
            <div class="collection-description">
        <p>John Herrman covers media for&#160;The New York Times Magazine. Previously, he was a reporter for the Business section&#160;and one of the first three recipients of The Times's David Carr Fellowship.</p>
<p>Before joining The Times, Mr. Herrman as a co-editor of The Awl and covered the Internet and technology at Gizmodo, Popular Mechanics and BuzzFeed.</p>
<p>A native of Cary, N.C., Mr. Herrman received his Master of Arts degree in English literature and philosophy from The University of Edinburgh, Scotland.</p>    </div>
    
    

    
